# =============================================================
# epublatejs — build-time LLM defaults
# =============================================================
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and uncomment the lines
# you want to seed. Vite picks the values up at build/dev start and
# bakes them into the resulting bundle as string literals.
#
# When the Settings → LLM row in IndexedDB is empty (first run on a
# device, fresh incognito window, after clearing site data), the
# values below are used to pre-fill the form. As soon as you click
# Save, the Dexie row owns the configuration and `.env` is no longer
# consulted. Curator state always wins.
#
# Only variables prefixed with `VITE_` reach the browser bundle —
# Vite drops anything else. See https://vite.dev/guide/env-and-mode.
#
# ----- SECURITY NOTICE ---------------------------------------
# Anything you set here lives in the JavaScript bundle the browser
# downloads. That's fine for `base_url`, `model`, and other harmless
# defaults. **It is NOT fine for an API key you wouldn't paste into
# the public web** — `VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_API_KEY` ends up in every
# deployed copy of your build.
#
# Recommended usage:
#   - Local dev / single-user deploy on a private endpoint:
#     setting `VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_API_KEY` is fine.
#   - Public deploy (Vercel preview, GitHub Pages, etc.):
#     leave it blank and let curators paste their own key into
#     Settings → LLM endpoint. That key lives only in their browser's
#     IndexedDB, never in your bundle.
# =============================================================

# Base URL of the OpenAI-compatible endpoint. Pick a preset to see
# the expected shape, or use one of the presets below.
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1

# API key. Sent as `Authorization: Bearer <key>`. Optional for Ollama
# (it ignores the header), required for OpenAI / OpenRouter / etc.
# DO NOT commit this to a public deploy — see the security notice
# above.
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_API_KEY=sk-...

# Translator model slug. The format is provider-specific:
#   OpenAI:      gpt-5-mini
#   OpenRouter:  openai/gpt-5-mini, deepseek/deepseek-v3.1, etc.
#   Ollama:      llama3.2, qwen3:14b, gpt-oss:20b, etc.
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_MODEL=gpt-5-mini

# Helper model used for tone-sniff, summaries, and other low-stakes
# helper LLM passes. Defaults to the translator model when blank.
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_HELPER_MODEL=gpt-5-nano

# Optional organization header (`OpenAI-Organization`). Most setups
# leave this blank.
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_ORGANIZATION=org-...

# Reasoning effort. One of:
#   minimal | low | medium | high   (OpenAI o-series convention)
#   none                             (Ollama-compat: disables thinking)
# Anything else is silently ignored.
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_REASONING_EFFORT=low

# Per-request HTTP timeout in milliseconds. Local Ollama with a
# thinking-capable model on a chapter-sized prompt routinely takes
# longer than the 60 000 ms default — bump this to 180 000 (3 min)
# or higher if you see Timeout errors in the LLM Activity log.
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_TIMEOUT_MS=180000

# =============================================================
# Reference: typical setups
# =============================================================
#
# --- OpenAI (hosted) ---
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_API_KEY=sk-...
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_MODEL=gpt-5-mini
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_HELPER_MODEL=gpt-5-nano
#
# --- OpenRouter (multi-model gateway) ---
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_API_KEY=sk-or-...
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_MODEL=openai/gpt-5-mini
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_HELPER_MODEL=openai/gpt-5-nano
#
# --- Ollama (local) ---
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
# # No API key needed; Ollama ignores Authorization.
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_MODEL=llama3.2
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_REASONING_EFFORT=none
# VITE_EPUBLATE_LLM_TIMEOUT_MS=180000
#
# Remember to start Ollama with the multi-scheme allow-list so the
# SPA's `https://` origin isn't rejected by its CORS layer:
#
#   export OLLAMA_ORIGINS="http://*,https://*,chrome-extension://*,moz-extension://*"
#   ollama serve
